---
layout: layout-base.njk
title: Crops That Lose the Most Margin When Planted Late | GrowByDate Data Rankings
description: A GrowByDate Data Ranking of crops that lose the most heat and maturity margin when planting slips by two weeks.
canonical: "https://growbydate.com/data/rankings/crops-that-lose-the-most-margin-when-planted-late/"
---

{% set board = cropsThatLoseMarginWhenPlantedLate %}
{% set top = board.top %}

<section class="card leaderboardHero">
  <p class="eyebrow">GrowByDate Data Ranking</p>
  <h1>Crops That Lose the Most Margin When Planted Late</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Some crops forgive a late start. Others quickly lose the heat margin they need before fall frost.
    This ranking compares crops by how much modeled GDD margin is lost when planting slips by two weeks.
  </p>

  <div class="leaderboardStatGrid" aria-label="Ranking summary">
    {% if top %}
      <div class="leaderboardStat">
        <span class="statLabel">Highest pressure crop</span>
        <strong>{{ top.cropName }}</strong>
        <span>{{ top.score }}/100 · {{ top.label }}</span>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

    <div class="leaderboardStat">
      <span class="statLabel">Dataset</span>
      <strong>{{ board.entries.length }} crops</strong>
      <span>Published crops with two-week delay data</span>
    </div>

    <div class="leaderboardStat">
      <span class="statLabel">Best used for</span>
      <strong>Late starts</strong>
      <span>Prioritizing crops when spring timing slips</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>The ranking</h2>
  <p>
    Crops rank higher when they lose more heat margin after a two-week planting delay, especially when that delay pushes more locations
    into negative maturity margin.
  </p>

  <div class="tableWrap leaderboardTableWrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Rank</th>
          <th>Crop</th>
          <th>Pressure score</th>
          <th>Two-week margin loss</th>
          <th>Avg. late margin</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for row in board.entries %}
          <tr>
            <td><strong>#{{ row.rank }}</strong></td>
            <td><strong>{{ row.cropName }}</strong><br><span class="small muted">{{ row.publishedLocations }} modeled locations</span></td>
            <td><strong>{{ row.score }}/100</strong></td>
            <td>{{ row.averageTwoWeekMarginLoss }} GDD</td>
            <td>{{ row.averageTwoWeekLateMargin }} GDD</td>
          </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Visual chart</h2>
  <p>
    For a more visual version of this ranking, see the <a href="/data/late-planting-penalty-chart/">Late Planting Penalty Chart</a>.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="card leaderboardCallout">
  <h2>What this ranking means</h2>
  <p>
    A high score does not mean the crop is impossible. It means late planting is more expensive: the crop loses more of its available heat window,
    and the difference between “probably fine” and “too tight” can shrink quickly.
  </p>
  <p>
    For a crop-specific answer, use the <a href="/tools/growing-degree-day-planner/">GDD planner</a> or compare the crop against
    <a href="/data/crop-heat-requirements/">Crop Heat Requirements</a>.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Methodology</h2>
  <p>{{ board.methodology }}</p>
  <p>{{ board.caveat }}</p>
  <p class="small">
    Data export: <a href="/assets/data/rankings/crops-that-lose-the-most-margin-when-planted-late.json">late-planting margin loss JSON</a>.
  </p>
</section>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "ItemList",
  "name": {{ board.title | dump | safe }},
  "description": {{ board.description | dump | safe }},
  "url": "https://growbydate.com/data/rankings/crops-that-lose-the-most-margin-when-planted-late/",
  "numberOfItems": {{ board.entries.length }},
  "itemListElement": [
    {% for row in board.entries %}
      {
        "@type": "ListItem",
        "position": {{ row.rank }},
        "name": {{ (row.cropName ~ " late-planting margin pressure") | dump | safe }}
      }{% if not loop.last %},{% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  ]
}
</script>
